<h1 style="text-align:center; color:#38bdf8;">Architectural Evolution</h1>

<p style="text-align:center; max-width:800px; margin:auto;">
My journey in software architecture reflects the evolution of technology itself — 
from standalone systems to distributed, cloud-native platforms. 
Each phase has shaped my understanding of scalability, complexity, and system design trade-offs.
</p>

<!-- SECTION -->
<div class="card">
    <h2>💻 Standalone Systems</h2>
    <p>
        Started with desktop-based applications where the entire system was self-contained.
        This phase built strong fundamentals in application design, performance, and direct user interaction.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2>🔗 Service-Based Architecture</h2>
    <p>
        Transitioned into service-oriented thinking by building web services in Java and .NET.
        This introduced concepts of separation of concerns, interoperability, and reusable services.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2>📡 WCF-Based Architecture</h2>
    <p>
        Worked extensively with WCF, enabling structured communication between systems.
        Focused on contracts, bindings, and service reliability in enterprise environments.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2>🌐 RESTful Architecture</h2>
    <p>
        Shifted towards REST-based services, designing lightweight, scalable APIs in Java.
        Embraced stateless communication, resource-oriented design, and web-scale principles.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2>⚙️ .NET Web API Architecture</h2>
    <p>
        Built modern API-driven systems using .NET Web API, enabling seamless integration,
        improved performance, and standardized service interfaces across platforms.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2>🖥️ Web Application Evolution</h2>
    <p>
        Transitioned from ASPX-based applications to ASP.NET, improving maintainability,
        scalability, and separation of UI and business logic.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2>⚡ Single Page Applications (SPA)</h2>
    <p>
        Adopted modern frontend paradigms using JavaScript and jQuery.
        Developed strong understanding of browser-side execution, asynchronous behavior,
        and rich user experience design.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2>🧠 Client & Server-Side JavaScript</h2>
    <p>
        Gained deep expertise in both client-side and server-side JavaScript,
        understanding execution models, performance considerations, and system interactions.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2>🌍 Microservices Architecture</h2>
    <p>
        Evolved into designing distributed microservices systems.
        Focused on scalability, resilience, service boundaries, and operational complexity.
        Learned critical trade-offs between flexibility and system complexity.
    </p>
</div>

<!-- INSIGHT -->
<div class="card">
    <h2>🧩 Key Insight</h2>
    <p>
        Architecture is not about following trends — it is about choosing the right approach
        based on context, scale, and business needs.
    </p>

    <p>
        My journey reinforced that:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Every architecture introduces trade-offs</li>
        <li>Complexity grows with distribution</li>
        <li>System thinking is essential for scalable design</li>
        <li>Context matters more than trends</li>
    </ul>
</div>

</section>
